---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Sam Onishi | Organizational Operations & Venture Support"
  description="Business and operations professional supporting founders and organizations in multilingual, cross-cultural environments."
>
  <div class="single-page">
    <section id="top" class="hero-section">
      <div class="hero-inner">
        <div class="hero-text">
          <p class="eyebrow">Operational Partner Profile</p>
          <h1>Sam Onishi</h1>
          <p class="subhead">Business Manager / Organizational Operations &amp; Venture Support (JA / EN / KO)</p>
          <p class="lead">
            Supporting founders, organizations, and creative initiatives in cross-cultural
            and multilingual environments—with a focus on structure, execution, and continuity.
          </p>
          <div class="hero-pills">
            <span>Organizational Operations</span>
            <span>Venture Support</span>
            <span>Localization &amp; Documentation</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-img-wrap">
          <img src="/hero-right.jpeg" alt="" width="800" height="600" />
          <span class="hero-caption">Cross-cultural execution in high-tempo environments</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="about" class="content-section">
      <h2>About</h2>
      <p class="section-lead">Operations-focused partner supporting founders and teams in cross-border and multilingual environments.</p>
      <figure class="section-img">
        <img src="/meetings.jpg" alt="Collaborative meeting" width="800" height="533" />
        <figcaption>Collaboration and coordination in practice</figcaption>
      </figure>
      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          Fluent in Japanese, English, and Korean, Sam works across organizational operations,
          program management, localization, and internal coordination—primarily in roles that
          strengthen structure and execution rather than public visibility.
        </p>
        <p>
          Over the course of his career, he has contributed to initiatives spanning Japan, Korea,
          Southeast Asia, and the United States, working within nonprofit, cultural, and early-stage
          venture contexts.
        </p>
        <p>
          Sam's approach centers on building practical foundations that allow founders and teams—
          particularly those navigating cross-border or non-native business environments—to focus on
          growth, creativity, and decision-making.
        </p>
        <h3>Focus Areas</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Organizational Operations &amp; Internal Coordination</li>
          <li>Program &amp; Venture Operations</li>
          <li>Localization &amp; Multilingual Communication (JA/EN/KO)</li>
          <li>Documentation &amp; Process Support</li>
          <li>Cross-border Coordination (Asia / North America)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="work" class="content-section">
      <h2>Work &amp; Background</h2>
      <p class="section-lead">Supporting and coordinating roles across cultural, creative, nonprofit, and corporate contexts.</p>
      <div class="work-intro prose">
        <p>
          Between 1995 and 2009, Sam was engaged in a wide range of independent, cross-border
          projects. He primarily worked in supporting and coordinating roles, helping bridge
          organizations, teams, and individuals operating across different countries, languages,
          and institutional environments.
        </p>
      </div>
      <figure class="section-img section-img--small">
        <img src="/organizer.png" alt="Cross-border operations and multilingual coordination" width="800" height="533" />
        <figcaption>Cross-border operations &amp; multilingual coordination</figcaption>
      </figure>
      <h3>Project Themes</h3>
      <div class="project-grid">
        <div class="project-card">
          <h4>Music &amp; Entertainment Project Support</h4>
          <p>Operational support in live performance settings, coordination among creative teams, alignment of expectations and workflows across cultural and organizational backgrounds.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="project-card">
          <h4>Digital &amp; Platform Support</h4>
          <p>Setup and management of websites and online platforms for international organizations, multilingual content organization and cross-border communication.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="project-card">
          <h4>Events, Festivals &amp; Live Production</h4>
          <p>Production and coordination of large-scale cultural events, festivals, international live productions—logistics, documentation, backstage operations.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="project-card">
          <h4>Environmental &amp; Community-Based Projects</h4>
          <p>Cross-border environmental and humanitarian initiatives connecting Japanese nonprofit organizations with stakeholders in Southeast Asia.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="project-card">
          <h4>Corporate &amp; Advertising Production</h4>
          <p>Support for advertising and production involving Japanese corporations operating overseas, coordination between corporate stakeholders and local creative teams.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="prose work-closing">
        <p>
          Across these projects, Sam consistently worked in roles that required navigating complexity
          between organizations from different countries and sectors, emphasizing structure,
          execution, and continuity over visibility or personal attribution.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="contact" class="content-section">
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p class="section-lead">For inquiries regarding organizational operations, venture support, or collaboration.</p>
      <p class="contact-email"><a href="mailto:contact@samonishi.com">contact@samonishi.com</a></p>
      <p class="contact-note">For updated professional information, please refer to <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/samonishi" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">LinkedIn</a>.</p>
    </section>

    <div class="context-strip">
      <figure><img src="/ABT-Web-Tile.png" alt="" /><figcaption>Creative &amp; cultural initiatives</figcaption></figure>
      <figure><img src="/500px-MCI_equipped_Studiod.jpg" alt="" /><figcaption>Execution &amp; production support</figcaption></figure>
    </div>
  </div>

  <style>
    .single-page {
      max-width: 680px;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }

    .hero-section {
      margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    }

    .hero-inner {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 1.5rem;
      align-items: start;
    }

    .eyebrow {
      font-size: 0.7rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      letter-spacing: 0.1em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--accent);
      margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    }

    .hero-text h1 {
      font-size: 1.75rem;
      margin: 0 0 0.35rem;
      font-weight: 400;
    }

    .subhead {
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      color: var(--muted);
      margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
    }

    .lead {
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      color: var(--muted);
      line-height: 1.6;
      margin: 0 0 1rem;
    }

    .hero-pills {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: 0.35rem 0.5rem;
    }

    .hero-pills span {
      font-size: 0.75rem;
      color: var(--accent);
      background: var(--accent-soft);
      padding: 0.2rem 0.5rem;
      border-radius: 4px;
    }

    .hero-img-wrap {
      position: relative;
      border-radius: 8px;
      overflow: hidden;
      background: var(--line);
      aspect-ratio: 4/3;
      max-height: 240px;
    }

    .hero-img-wrap img {
      width: 100%;
      height: 100%;
      object-fit: cover;
      display: block;
    }

    .hero-caption {
      position: absolute;
      left: 0.75rem;
      bottom: 0.75rem;
      padding: 0.25rem 0.5rem;
      background: rgba(0,0,0,0.6);
      color: #fff;
      font-size: 0.7rem;
      border-radius: 4px;
    }

    .content-section {
      margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
      padding-top: 0.5rem;
    }

    .content-section h2 {
      font-size: 1.35rem;
      font-weight: 400;
      margin: 0 0 0.35rem;
      padding-bottom: 0.25rem;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
    }

    .section-lead {
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      color: var(--muted);
      margin: 0 0 1rem;
    }

    .section-img {
      margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
      max-width: 400px;
      border-radius: 8px;
      overflow: hidden;
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
    }

    .section-img img {
      width: 100%;
      height: auto;
      display: block;
    }

    .section-img figcaption {
      padding: 0.4rem 0.6rem;
      font-size: 0.75rem;
      color: var(--muted);
      background: var(--surface);
      border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
    }

    .prose {
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .prose p {
      margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      line-height: 1.65;
    }

    .prose h3 {
      font-size: 1rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      margin: 1rem 0 0.5rem;
    }

    .prose ul {
      margin: 0 0 1rem;
      padding-left: 1.25rem;
    }

    .prose li {
      margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
    }

    .work-intro {
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .project-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 0.75rem 1rem;
      margin: 1rem 0;
    }

    .project-card {
      padding: 0.9rem;
      background: var(--surface);
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: 8px;
    }

    .project-card h4 {
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      margin: 0 0 0.35rem;
    }

    .project-card p {
      font-size: 0.85rem;
      color: var(--muted);
      margin: 0;
      line-height: 1.5;
    }

    .work-closing {
      margin-top: 1rem;
    }

    .contact-email {
      font-size: 1rem;
      margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    }

    .contact-email a {
      font-weight: 600;
    }

    .contact-note {
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      color: var(--muted);
    }

    .context-strip {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 0.75rem;
      margin-top: 2rem;
      padding-top: 1.5rem;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
    }

    .context-strip figure {
      margin: 0;
      border-radius: 8px;
      overflow: hidden;
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
    }

    .context-strip img {
      width: 100%;
      height: auto;
      display: block;
      max-height: 140px;
      object-fit: cover;
    }

    .context-strip figcaption {
      padding: 0.35rem 0.5rem;
      font-size: 0.7rem;
      color: var(--muted);
      background: var(--surface);
      border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
    }

    @media (max-width: 640px) {
      .hero-inner {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }

      .hero-img-wrap {
        max-height: 200px;
      }

      .project-grid {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }

      .context-strip {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
